This paper is about medical image segmentation using a novel method called Hierarchical Attention Network (HANet). The paper proposes a self-attention mechanism that captures context information from neighbors of multiple levels, which is a common approach in computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG, cs.AI). The paper also deals with the challenges of noisy and variable medical images, which are common in multimedia (cs.MM) and neural networks (cs.NE). Therefore, the most likely arXiv CS sub-category for this paper is cs.CV, followed by cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM, and cs.NE.
